description:
Sponsored by State Farm®

Founded by artist and entrepreneur Najee Dorsey,  Black Art In America (BAIA) is on a mission to document, preserve, and promote African American art. Over the last 15 years, Najee has built a multifaceted organization that includes an art gallery, media platform, educational programming, curation, and traveling art experiences. In addition to platforming artists, his goal is to make art collecting accessible and empowering for everyday people.

Curating exhibitions, hosting events, and selling art carry many challenges and risks. Najee’s relationship with his State Farm agent, Natalie, has been critical to protecting the foundation he’s worked so hard to build. 
 
Learn how a State Farm agent can help you choose the options you need as a small business owner: https://www.statefarm.com/general/small-business-a
